This paper deals with the problem of ranking Twitter accounts based on their prospective popularity, which involves analyzing the social network structure of Twitter. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves analyzing the content of tweets and identifying early adopters, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for link inference, which could fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses the use of crawling techniques to obtain information about the Twitter graph, which could fall under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity).
